Good. Now let me also check if there's an issue with the `_autoSpin` initialization. When `AutoSpin` getter returns `_autoSpin` instead of `_timeout != null`, we need to make sure `_autoSpin` is properly updated when `RemoveAutoSpinTimeout` is called (e.g., from `Dispose`). Looking at `Dispose`:

```csharp
protected override void Dispose (bool disposing)
{
    RemoveAutoSpinTimeout ();
    base.Dispose (disposing);
}
```

And `RemoveAutoSpinTimeout`:
```csharp
private void RemoveAutoSpinTimeout ()
{
    if (_timeout is { })
    {
        App?.RemoveTimeout (_timeout);
        _timeout = null;
    }
}
```

It doesn't set `_autoSpin = false`. But that's OK because in `Dispose`, the view is being disposed anyway, so `_autoSpin` doesn't matter. And the `AutoSpin` setter calls `RemoveAutoSpinTimeout()` when the user sets `AutoSpin = false`.

Now let me build and run the existing tests:

